		"description": "<p dir=\"ltr\">You&rsquo;ve learned even more tricks to keep your enemies (and sometimes your allies) guessing. You gain the following benefits:</p>\n<ul>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">Your prestige rating is treated as 2 higher among pirates, criminals, and other underworld types and as 1 lower for nobility, merchants, and others of high status.</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">You can spend a use of @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.m7siz0z3rlng8h20]{Bardic Inspiration} to raise the DC of an illusion or enchantment spell you cast by 1. Once you have used this benefit twice, you can&rsquo;t do so again until you finish a long rest. This benefit does not stack with other similar effects.</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">When you use @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.hd5w4jpsyvtkunwg]{Art Mastery} with the Visual option, you can choose to become invisible until the beginning of your next turn.&nbsp;</p>\n</li>\n<li dir=\"ltr\" aria-level=\"1\">\n<p dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">If you reduce a creature with a CR equal to at least half your level to 0 hit points with an attack where you dealt @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.4727pnvz5nwn3h23]{Sneak Attack} damage, you regain a use of Bardic Inspiration. You cannot exceed your normal maximum uses of Bardic Inspiration available with this benefit. Once you have used this benefit a number of times equal to your Charisma modifier, you can&rsquo;t do so again until you finish a long rest.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
